{
  "text": "The instrument asks the following question. Rise and glad the instrument is on the path of martyrdom, but since all die, are we not all martyred to something? When, if ever, does martyrdom partake of wisdom? I am this is a thoughtful query. Let us use as exemplar the one known as Jahoshua, this entity incarnated with the plan of martyrdom. There is no wisdom in this plan about rather understanding and compassion extended to its fullest perfection. The one known as Jehashua would have been less than fully understanding of its course. Had it chosen to follow its will at any space time during its teachings, several times as you call this measure. This entity had the possibility of moving towards the martyr's place which was for that martyr Jarusala. Yet in meditation this entity stated time and egging. So that all mind, a body, a spirit complexes shall addie to the third density illusion. That is that each yellow ray, a physical, a complex, a body, shall cease to be reliable. It is a misnomer to for this reason alone, call each mind, body, spirit, complex a martyr. For this term is reserved for those who lay down their lives for the service they may provide to others. Meditation upon the functions of the will.",
  "timestamps": {
